Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni. Meanwhile, halve any large @broccoli florets{200%g}. When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook for ~{7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). In a #small bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then set aside.

Heat your #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When the pasta has been cooking for 7 mins, add the broccoli florets to the pan and bring back to the boil. Cook with the pasta until tender, ~{5%minutes} more. Once cooked, drain well in a #colander{}.

In the meantime, once the sauce has thickened, stir in the Cheddar, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @Dijon mustard{10%g} until melted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

Stir the cooked pasta and broccoli into the sauce, then transfer it into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Sprinkle over the crumbs, then pop under the grill until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the crumbs carefully as they can burn easily.

When the broccoli pasta bake is ready, share it out between your plates. Serve the @baby leaf mix{20%g} alongside and drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over them to finish. Enjoy!